          "prompt": {
            "en": "[@tool:generate_image_gpt_image_2:GPT Image 2 Auto:https://lovart-persist-us.oss-us-east-1.aliyuncs.com/web/icon/chatgpt.svg][@skill:branding_logo:Logo & Branding:https://assets-persist.lovart.ai/web/icon-skill-branding.svg] [@image:#1:product sealed:https://a.lovart.ai/artifacts/user/Rm6A1tvvjDGmZJKl.png][@image:#2:product open:https://a.lovart.ai/artifacts/user/oMSavB21dG2yHFFj.png] SYSTEM ROLE: You are an AI image generation engine responsible for producing a complete and consistent brand visual system. You generate images only. You must build the system step by step, and each stage defines constraints for the next stage.

INPUT LAYER (SOURCE OF TRUTH): Use only the provided product information and product images. Brand: FJÄLL (Sweden). Product: Midnight Solstice Hand Cream (75ml). Core Identity: Mineral-based functional hand performance system with a non-cosmetic positioning but refined beauty sensorial expression. Key Functional Claims: silky glide sensorial performance, zero residue, fast absorption, barrier defense. Material System: volcanic mineral extract, purified clay complex, Nordic botanicals. Texture Behavior: dense → resistant spread → controlled breakdown → matte dry-down. Brand Tone: technical, minimal, controlled, Nordic (clean, calm, natural, restrained).

GLOBAL CONSTRAINTS: Use provided product images as the base prototype and do not modify product structure, proportions, or label. Do not invent new product variations. Avoid decorative, luxury, or overly expressive styling, and avoid exaggerated industrial or futuristic sci-fi aesthetics. All visuals must balance function with a Nordic skincare sensibility. Material rendering must remain matte and controlled with no artificial shine or glossy cosmetic finish. All text must be in English and remain readable, stable, and sharp.

VISUAL CONSISTENCY: All outputs must share soft, diffused Nordic natural lighting, a neutral and desaturated color system, and calm contrast without harsh highlights. Material behavior must feel real, subtle, and controlled. Human elements must appear clean, healthy, dry (non-greasy), and natural without stylization or dramatic treatment. No style reset is allowed between phases.

GENERATION STRATEGY: You must generate outputs in strict order. Each phase defines rules for the next. Do not skip or reorder any phase.

PHASE 0 — LOGO SYSTEM: Output 2–3 variations in 1:1 ratio. Define a brand identity that reflects a Nordic skincare product rather than a tech or engineering brand. Balance functional clarity, subtle skincare softness, and Nordic minimalism. Avoid overly technical, mechanical, industrial, sci-fi, or high-tech visual language. The symbol should feel simple, calm, refined, and lightweight but structured. Typography must be sans-serif, minimal, elegant, restrained, and highly legible, with no aggressive geometry or heavy industrial construction. No decorative elements, but allow slight organic softness in proportion. Background must be clean, soft, and neutral. This phase defines typography, spacing, and tone for all later outputs.

PHASE 1 — PRODUCT FOUNDATION: Output 1 image in 1:1 ratio. Establish a product baseline aligned with Nordic skincare tone using soft diffused lighting and a neutral calm background. Avoid harsh industrial environments and dramatic shadows or contrast. Maintain product realism and cleanliness.

PHASE 2 — FUNCTIONAL KEY VISUAL: Output 1 image in 4:5 ratio. Show functional performance in a natural and believable context with cosmetic sensorial elegance. Hand interaction must feel real and subtle, emphasizing smooth silky application behavior. Use natural materials such as stone, wood, or mineral surfaces and avoid heavy industrial or aggressive mechanical scenes. Maintain Nordic calmness and restraint.

PHASE 3 — TECHNICAL POSTER: Output 1 image in 2:3 ratio. Communicate function in a structured but calm way using a clean grid layout with minimal technical callouts. Avoid dense engineering diagrams and maintain clarity with sufficient breathing space.

PHASE 4 — E-COMMERCE SYSTEM: Output 3 images in 1:1 ratio. Maintain Nordic clarity and strong product focus. Texture, comparison, and ingredient logic must remain clean, readable, and non-aggressive.

PHASE 5 — SOCIAL MEDIA SYSTEM: Output 3 images in strict 9:16 vertical format at 1080x1920 resolution. All outputs must be realistic iOS-style mobile screenshots with no Dynamic Island, no notch, and no Android UI elements, using a clean full rectangular screen frame. Interface must feel native, minimal, and modern. Image 1: feed interface with top status indicators, showing smooth application transition with slightly increasing metrics while keeping text stable and readable. Image 2: full-screen story interface with minimal UI and subtle interaction, no clutter. Image 3: post detail screen with carousel-style content showing step-by-step texture transformation, ensuring UI does not overpower content.

OUTPUT CONTROL: Generate images only, follow sequence strictly, and do not reset style. All outputs must feel like one unified Nordic skincare brand system. Typography must be sharp, clean, and perfectly legible with no distortion or artifacts. Human faces must be natural, undistorted, realistic, and not exaggerated or stylized."
          },
