          "prompt": {
            "en": "[@tool:generate_image_gpt_image_2:GPT Image 2 Auto:https://lovart-persist-us.oss-us-east-1.aliyuncs.com/web/icon/chatgpt.svg]Generate the following 8 images, requiring a 4:3 aspect ratio. all person is [@image:#1:image:https://a.lovart.ai/artifacts/user/Tq1RapoopI86kTYO.png].

An open cardboard shipping carton filled with a mix of blue and clear bubble wrap cushioning and some small gadgets. Prominently featured in the foreground is a detailed, printed white retail product box for "90s beats" headphones. The box cover features a portrait of a person wearing white headphones with rose gold circular details and a pink "S" logo. The main text on the box reads "90s beats⁴" in black and red, with a red corner sticker labeled "SUPER Q VOLUME 4". Bottom text includes "ULTRA FIT", "PURE ANC 22HOUR", and "EXCLUSIVE EVERYDAY HEADSET™ X404 INTERNATIONAL". Detailed multilingual text (Arabic, Japanese, and European languages) and hercules support URLs are clearly legible on the left side panel of the box. Behind the box, there is a larger DJ turntable covered with star stickers, partially wrapped in bubble wrap, along with some vintage millennium dolls next to the box. A high-angle detailed product photograph, in a realistic style, featuring a bit of old-school CCD direct flash. The tactile textures of cardboard, paper, and crinkled plastic, in a 4:3 aspect ratio.

A high-resolution, realistic first-person perspective (POV) photograph, taken from a direct, high angle looking down at a pink carpeted floor with three magazines, nail polish, a comb, and lipstick on it. The photographer's knees, visible through trousers, are visible in the frame (enhancing the subjective visual effect). Saturated colors and the style of early 2000s CCD direct flash photography define the scene. The three tactile paper magazines are fanned out from left to right, partially overlapping. The leftmost magazine's cover is "Bratz" Fashion Pixiez, featuring a large, retro purple and pink headline. The cover showcases a Bratz doll resembling a person's design. Specific details on the cover include: "Fashion Special!", "Plus! Hot Celebrity Gossip, Bratz Secrets, and More!", "Hot New Bratz Posters!", and "How to Shop Smart!" (right side), "Bratz Spring/Summer 2000 Fashion Secrets!", "Free! BRATZ FASHION PIXIEZ Tattoo!" (top left), and a small illustrated portrait of Jojo (bottom left), captioned "Bratz Interview! JOJO!". The central magazine cover features a "2000s" Moira holiday look with a large pink/purple glitter headline and stars. The cover features a close-up of the person face, with the main title "Frost and Gloss" in pink glitter text, and the slogan "Frosty eyelids, full lips, and a shimmer that catches every camera flash." Specific product details include an eyeshadow palette labeled "Limited Edition Diamond Glitter Eyeshadow Palette," a "New Product Fashion Silky Lipstick" labeled 002 Y2K, and a black circular label labeled "Ten Years of Makeup Vol. 5."The rightmost magazine is a vibrant 2000s Y2K Japanese fashion magazine, Gyaru. The top section shows the person playfully sitting on a blue metallic bench in a nighttime amusement park, with a blurred, illuminated Ferris wheel behind them. Large neon pink and yellow text on the right reads "JSG $HIN¥ DRØP$ Summer 2000," while the bottom left is decorated with graphic shooting stars. The bottom quarter of the poster features a horizontal grid of five square catalog photos showcasing colorful Y2K clothing and accessories against a bright yellow and pink background, with a footer containing small promotional text and a QR code.The magazine's barcode is at the bottom. Soft overhead lighting, in a 4:3 aspect ratio.

A realistic first-person point-of-view photograph showing a fast-food meal resting on a black plastic tray, shot with a nostalgic, low-saturation early digital camera (CCD) effect with slight grain and direct flash. The tray holds a custom Y2K pop-star branded meal set. On the left is a plastic cup filled with dark iced soda and a clear domed lid, featuring a green graphic sleeve printed with a person, with a paper-wrapped straw lying flat in front. Behind it sits a cardboard gable box decorated with 2000s-style stars, concentric circles, and cyan, pink, and blue polka dots, featuring a half-body image of the person in a fashionable pose with hands on hips. To the right foreground is a rectangular magenta and green burger box displaying a full-body image of the person. The subtly blurred background reveals typical fast-food restaurant decor with beige floor tiles and red metal-framed chairs under warm indoor lighting, in a 4:3 aspect ratio.

In a high-resolution overhead close-up photo, a fully open, silver-blue Nintendo Game Boy Advance SP handheld console lies quietly on a concrete floor. The screen is lit, displaying a retro person selfie : winks one eye. The console's casing and edges are adorned with colorful rhinestones, beads, and sequins, exuding a strong millennial DIY vibe. On the lower control panel, besides the standard gray directional pad, A/B buttons, and SELECT/START markings, there are scattered glittery pink cat stickers, rainbow stickers, and green star sequins. The CCD's low-saturation texture, with direct light casting shimmering shadows on the rhinestones and stickers, also clearly outlines the carpet's velvety texture. The entire image is retro yet sharp, in a 4:3 aspect ratio.

This is a finely detailed macro photograph with a low-saturation, vintage feel, reminiscent of a direct CCD flash. Slightly overexposed, it showcases an intricate keychain hanging from a pair of light blue washed vintage jeans. The image focuses directly on the texture of the denim and the keychain itself. These elements converge above a central frame: a thin chain, a cord adorned with various sizes of small heart-shaped beads and star-shaped beads, a textured gold heart pendant, and white star pendants, along with one or two keys and a Tamagotchi (random color). Below these pendants is a transparent acrylic frame pendant, connected by a thin chain. Within the frame is a clear, full image of a person: the texture of the dark denim and the striking yellow stitching. The flash illuminates the image, highlighting the various textures of the metal, acrylic, wiring, and denim, in a 4:3 aspect ratio.

This is a retro, early 2000s lo-fi flash overhead CCD photo capturing a nostalgic scene. On a slightly wrinkled white cotton sheet sits a silver Sony Walkman Discman portable CD player with clearly visible purple "SONY" and "WALKMAN" logos. A pair of black wired earphones (with L-shaped plugs) are connected to the player, the wires dangling between the player and the CD case. To its right is a closed album CD case. The album cover is pink and white, featuring the person figure and heart, skull, and crossbones patterns. A striking pink label sticker on the cover bears legible text including "back to the 90s" and "the new album from xxx the best damn thing." The entire scene is illuminated by direct flash, giving it a film grain and retro feel, with the earphone wires crossing below, in a 4:3 aspect ratio.

This is a retro Y2K, early 2000s lo-fi flash overhead CCD photo capturing a nostalgic scene. It showcases a 90s office coffee corner, with a large, reflective silver automatic beverage machine at its center, adorned with stickers. A tower of coffee cups of varying sizes is irregularly stacked on top of the machine. The machine's color screen clearly displays a person.She holds a white espresso cup and saucer. A red digital display at the top of the screen shows "000." Below the screen are several buttons with printed text: left for (milk coffee), right for (hot chocolate), and other control buttons in the middle. In the dispensing area below the machine, a pink coffee cup contains a hot beverage, with a blue LED indicator below it. To the left of the machine, a smaller silver stainless steel coffee machine (with a "dr" logo) is visible. To the right of the machine, a black metal basket contains small packets and a wooden stirrer, along with several stacks of lidded paper cups with dark and gold prints. Further away is a glass filled with red decorations (such as fruit skewers or a blender). The background consists of white walls and a door. The composition is a direct view of the machine, with bright office lighting, in a 4:3 aspect ratio.

This is a retro, early 2000s lo-fi flash CCD photo taken from above, capturing a nostalgic scene. It showcases a standing, portable white Gashapon gashapon machine, flanked by other gashapon machines of different styles. A keyhole is located on top. In the center is a large, transparent display case containing several brightly colored gashapon capsules (purple and green). The main subject on the poster is a person.The display poster on the case is striking: the number is centered on the image. At the top of the poster is the gold artistic font "rainbow bears," below which are three different colored Y2K bears (pink, yellow, and blue). The lower part of the machine features a silver coin slot and a rotating crank, as well as a circular gashapon outlet with a transparent cover. The machine has a white base and wheels. The background is a vibrant pink and purple wall with a blurred planet pattern, and the floor is gray tile with wooden trim. The interior lighting is clear and even, in a 4:3 aspect ratio."
